File: Electricity switched off. Flickr/Paul Cross JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has announced stage 2 power cuts will be implemented from 5pm until 10pm every day this week. The power utility says this is due to a shortage of generation capacity. There is a possibility that power cuts might be implemented outside of these hours. Stage 3 power cuts are currently underway until 10pm. #PowerAlert2
Due to the continued shortage of generation capacity, Stage 2 loadshedding will be implemented from 17:00 until 22:00 throughout the week. pic.twitter.com/E40GBxaAjs